- Group A Streptococcal (GAS) Disease [https://www.cdc.gov/groupastrep/index.html]
- Streptococcal Toxic Shock Syndrome: For Clinicians [https://www.cdc.gov/groupastrep/diseases-hcp/Streptococcal-Toxic-Shock-Syndrome.html]
- Type II Necrotizing Fasciitis: Inform Serious non-suppurative sequelae, such as acute rheumatic fever and rheumatic heart disease, and glomerulonephritis may also occur after GAS pharyngitis. Information For Clinicians [https://www.cdc.gov/groupastrep/diseases-hcp/necrotizing-fasciitis.html]
- Pharyngitis (Strep Throat): Information For Clinicians [https://www.cdc.gov/groupastrep/diseases-hcp/strep-throat.html]

References
----------
